Business Brief -- Ashland Oil Inc.:
   Chemical Unit Will Expand
   Facility at Neal, W.Va.
The expansion will increase the plant's production of the
petrochemical to about 90 million pounds annually from its
current production rate of 63 million pounds.
   The Ashland, Ky., company said it expects construction at
the Neal plant to begin early this year. Startup of the
expanded facilities is scheduled for mid-1993.
   Ashland Chemical, based in Columbus, Ohio, makes
chemicals, petrochemicals and plastics.